{"questionId":"11734","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The curve&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is shown in the graph, for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 \\leqslant x \\leqslant 10\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/0a44fa05389ed914ed86a1ea66c71882666a4a36.png\"></p>\n<p>The curve&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;passes through the following points.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/adf9974b6e26c279a59fd52f8b99005acb9af1e3.png\"></p>\n<p>It is required to find the area bounded by the curve, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span><em>-</em>axis, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span><em>-</em>axis and the line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 10\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One possible model for the curve&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is a cubic function.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down an expression for the area enclosed by the cubic regression curve, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and the line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 10\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Area =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int\\limits_0^{10} {y\\,dx} \">\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11734","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.12c.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down an expression for the area enclosed by the cubic regression curve, the x -axis, the y -axis and the line x = 10 .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.8—Trapezoid rule","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}